    Calories and Nutrients In The Food Items Of Trending Fast Food Joints

    fastfoodcalories.Rd

    Calories and Nutrients In The Food Items Of Trending Fast Food Joints

    Usage

    fastfoodcalories

    Format

    A data frame with 515 observations and 28 variables.

    ...1

    A unique identifier for each data entry.

    restaurant

    The name of the fast-food restaurant.

    item

    The name of the food item from the restaurant's menu.

    calories

    The calorie content of the food item.

    cal_fat

    The calorie content from fat in the food item.

    total_fat

    The total fat content in the food item.

    sat_fat

    The saturated fat content in the food item.

    trans_fat

    The trans fat content in the food item.

    cholesterol

    The cholesterol content in the food item.

    sodium

    The sodium content in the food item.

    total_carb

    The total carbohydrate content in the food item.

    fiber

    The dietary fiber content in the food item.

    sugar

    The sugar content in the food item.

    protein

    The protein content in the food item.

    vit_a

    The vitamin A content in the food item.

    vit_c

    The vitamin C content in the food item.

    calcium

    The calcium content in the food item.

    salad

    A categorization of whether the food item is a salad or not.

    carb_percent

    The percentage of total carbohydrates in the food item.

    protein_percent

    The percentage of protein in the food item.

    fiber_percent

    The percentage of dietary fiber in the food item.

    vit_a_percent

    The percentage of vitamin A in the food item.

    vit_c_percent

    The percentage of vitamin C in the food item.

    calcium_percent

    The percentage of calcium in the food item.

    cholesterol_percent

    The percentage of cholesterol in the food item.

    sugar_percent

    The percentage of sugar in the food item.

    sodium_percent

    The percentage of sodium in the food item.

    sat_fat_percentage

    The percentage of saturated fat in the food item.

    Source

    https://github.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/blob/master/data/2018/2018-09-04/fastfood_calories.csv
